dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Create the county zoning map as required by the Polk County Zoning Ordinances.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents zoning for Polk County, Wisconsin in 2013. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, “Polk_Zoning_2013.gdb”. [This dataset designates the zoning district for geographical areas in Polk County. The data set is a compilation of multiple internal data sets including 'ZoningComp', 'ZoningShoreland', 'ZoneGenPur', and 'ZoningWet'.]
